    • git diff
      
    • git show e40cce74e2c509e48b863a75a5bbd97ff1c8ad7f:index.html 
(git show commit id:file path in local repo) 
(It show the code in the commit with given commit id)
      
    • git checkout 65be6a700b9f877ae46273ddae1111f91f907fb4 -- */index.html
(use asterik to add all files or give the file name)
(It will bring back the code which was committed within this commit id)

    • git checkout master -- *
       
Negative case scenario commands: 
	In case some wrong changes are saved in the file or added to the git.

    • git restore ./file name (dot/file name) (restore to last working version of file)
    • git diff –cached (It will show the difference in the file after “git add” )
    • git restore --staged . (It will revert the code like before “git add” command)
    • git restore --worktree */index.html (if we “git add” the file, after this there’s some mistake in the error and this command will undo changes to the file after adding it to the git)
    • git reset --soft HEAD^ (Uncommit and keep the changes)
    • git reset --hard HEAD^ (Uncommit and but discard the changes)


Useful Log Options
    • git log -p -2 (last two commit with diff)
    • git log --stat (summary of changes)
    • git log --pretty=oneline
    • git log --pretty=format:"%h - %an, %ar : %s"
    • git log -S function_name
    • git log --grep="fix bug" (search commit msg)
    • git log --since="2024-01-01"
    • git log --until="2024-01-01"
    • git log --author="Ghufran"
    • git log --no-merges
